Welcome to LibBbrc.

Please choose:
a) Refer to http://www.maunz.de/libbbrc-doc/ for installation instructions on various platforms. 
b) Build the documentation yourself with doxygen: type 'make doc'.

Contents of the above documentation:
- Links to scientific paper and abstract
- Installation (several OS and languages)
- Example program using the LibBbrc API
- Description of Constructors and Options
- Official contact information

For a quickstart try:
$ ./configure
$ make
$ make test

Andreas Maunz, 2010
